    • Method Detail

      • setup

        void setup()
        Setups anything that is needed for this command.

        It is recommended you do the following in this method:
        • Register any of the sub-commands of this command;
        • Define the permission required to use this command using CompositeCommand.setPermission(String);
        • Define whether this command can only be run by players or not using CompositeCommand.setOnlyPlayer(boolean);

      • canExecute

        default boolean canExecute(User user,
                           String label,
                           List<String> args)
        Returns whether the command can be executed by this user or not. It is recommended to send messages to let this user know why they could not execute the command. Note that this is run previous to execute(User, String, List).
        Parameters:
        user - the User who is executing this command.
        label - the label which has been used to execute this command. It can be Command.getLabel() or an alias.
        args - the command arguments.
        Returns:
        true if this command can be executed, false otherwise.
        Since:
        1.3.0

      • execute

        boolean execute(User user,
                String label,
                List<String> args)
        Defines what will be executed when this command is run.
        Parameters:
        user - the User who is executing this command.
        label - the label which has been used to execute this command. It can be Command.getLabel() or an alias.
        args - the command arguments.
        Returns:
        true if the command executed successfully, false otherwise.

      • tabComplete

        default Optional<List<String>> tabComplete(User user,
                                           String alias,
                                           List<String> args)
        Tab Completer for CompositeCommands. Note that any registered sub-commands will be automatically added to the list. Use this to add tab-complete for things like names.
        Parameters:
        user - the User who is executing this command.
        alias - alias for command
        args - command arguments
        Returns:
        List of strings that could be used to complete this command.
